
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-mpls-ldp-hello-crypto-auth-10.txt'>
    <title>"LDP Hello Cryptographic Authentication", Lianshu Zheng, Mach Chen, Manav Bhatia</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-mpls-ldp-hello-crypto-auth-10.txt</link>
    <description>This document introduces a new optional Cryptographic Authentication TLV that LDP can use to secure its Hello messages.  It secures the Hello messages against spoofing attacks and some well known attacks against the IP header.  This document describes a mechanism to secure the LDP Hello messages using Hashed Message Authentication Code (HMAC) with National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) Secure Hash Standard family of algorithms.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-06-19T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
